<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-17T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-17T18:00:00-05:00" n="896" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d896">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M) Turkey/1021c</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-17T19:00:00-04:00">April
                                        17, 1944—7 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>340. Last week British Embassy here submitted memorandum detailing
                                recent and prospective steps being taken by your British colleague
                                with respect to chrome and requested, if Department agreed, that you
                                be similarly instructed. Department replied that you were fully
                                aware of importance attached to chrome and amply authorized to
                                support your British colleague at all times in manner in your joint
                                judgment deemed most effective.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>